\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {12}{\ignorespaces Comparison of FMR resonance curves for different sweep rates. The black graph corresponds to the slow sweep rate (0.05 A/min) and higher time constant (1s), while the red graph corresponds to the fast sweep rate (0.1 A/s) and lower time constant (300 ms). The slow sweep rate provides better signal quality but takes longer to acquire data, while the fast sweep rate allows for quicker measurements but may introduce more noise.\relax }}{18}{figure.caption.12}\protected@file@percent }
